      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: May 25, 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>Legacy Odyssey ("Legacy Odyssey," "we," "us," or "our") is a digital baby book platform operated by <strong>DOR Industries</strong>, based in Mesa, Arizona, USA. For the purposes of the EU and UK General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR / UK GDPR), DOR Industries is the <strong>data controller</strong> for personal data processed through the Service.</p>
      <p>The content you share with us is deeply personal — photos of your children, family stories, and cherished memories — and we take protecting it seriously. This Privacy Policy explains what we collect, why, the legal bases we rely on, who we share it with, how long we keep it, and the rights you have.</p>
      <p><strong>Contact for privacy matters:</strong> <a href="mailto:help@legacyodyssey.com">help@legacyodyssey.com</a>.</p>

      <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>2.1 Account information</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Password (stored only as a salted hash; we never see your plain-text password)</li>
        <li>Display name (optional)</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.2 Book content you provide</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Photos and images</li>
        <li>Text content (stories, letters, recipes, milestones)</li>
        <li>Child information (name, birth date, birth details)</li>
        <li>Family member information (names, relationships)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Some of this content relates to <strong>children</strong>. You provide it as the parent or legal guardian — see Section 11.</p>
      <h3>2.3 Payment information</h3>
      <p>Payments are processed by Stripe, Inc. We do <strong>not</strong> store your full card number, bank details, or other sensitive payment credentials on our servers. We retain limited billing records (e.g., transaction IDs, amounts, dates) for accounting and tax purposes.</p>
      <h3>2.4 Domain information</h3>
      <p>If you claim a custom domain, we collect the domain name you choose and the registrant details required to register it. Registration is handled by our registrar partner (Spaceship), subject to their privacy policy and to ICANN requirements.</p>
      <h3>2.5 Technical &amp; usage information</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address, browser type and version, device type</li>
        <li>Pages visited and actions taken within the Service</li>
        <li>Date and time of access</li>
        <li>Information collected via cookies and similar technologies (see Section 5)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. How we use your information &amp; legal bases</h2>
      <p>Where GDPR / UK GDPR applies, we rely on the following legal bases (Article 6):</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>To provide the Service</strong> (host your book, store content, manage your account) — <em>performance of a contract</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>To process payments and manage subscriptions and domains</strong> — <em>performance of a contract</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>To send service emails</strong> (welcome, password reset, billing, important notices) — <em>performance of a contract</em> / <em>legitimate interests</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>To keep records and meet tax, accounting, and legal obligations</strong> — <em>legal obligation</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>For analytics, advertising, and marketing cookies/pixels</strong> — <em>your consent</em> (which you can withdraw at any time).</li>
        <li><strong>To secure the Service and prevent abuse</strong> — <em>legitimate interests</em>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. How we protect your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Encryption in transit:</strong> all traffic is served over HTTPS/TLS.</li>
        <li><strong>Encryption at rest &amp; secure storage:</strong> data is stored with Supabase, which provides encryption at rest and regular backups.</li>
        <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> only authorized personnel can access your data, and only when needed to provide support or operate the Service.</li>
        <li><strong>Password-protected books:</strong> published books are private and visible only to people you give the password to; they are not indexed by search engines.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Cookies &amp; tracking technologies</h2>
      <p>We use the following categories of cookies and similar technologies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Strictly necessary (always on):</strong> to keep you signed in to your account, and to remember that a book visitor has entered the correct password so they don't have to re-enter it on every page.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics (consent-based):</strong> Google Analytics 4 and Hotjar/Contentsquare, to understand how the site is used and improve it.</li>
        <li><strong>Advertising &amp; marketing (consent-based):</strong> Meta (Facebook) Pixel, Pinterest Tag, and Google AdSense, to measure and improve our advertising.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>For visitors in the EU, UK, and other regions that require it, non-essential (analytics and advertising) cookies are loaded <strong>only after you consent</strong> via our cookie banner, and you can change or withdraw your choice at any time. You can also control cookies through your browser settings. Strictly necessary cookies do not require consent.</p>

      <h2>6. How we share your information</h2>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or trade your personal information. We share it only with service providers who process data on our behalf (our "processors" / "sub-processors"), under data processing agreements, and where required by law.</p>
      <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:1rem 0;">
        <thead><tr><th style="text-align:left;padding:6px 8px;">Provider</th><th style="text-align:left;padding:6px 8px;">Purpose</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Stripe</td><td style="padding:6px 8px;">Payment processing (<a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">policy</a>)</td></tr>
