        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>We may also disclose information if required by law, court order, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of our users or others.</p>

      <h2>7. International data transfers</h2>
      <p>We are based in the United States, and our providers may store and process data in the U.S. and other countries. If you are in the EU, UK, or another region with data-transfer restrictions, your data may be transferred outside your home country. Where required, such transfers rely on appropriate safeguards such as the European Commission's Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or equivalent mechanisms offered by our providers.</p>

      <h2>8. Data retention</h2>
      <p>We keep your account and book content for as long as your subscription is active. When your subscription ends — whether you cancel or it is not renewed — you keep access through the end of the period you have paid for. After that, your website goes offline and the associated domain is released. We then keep your photos and stories for up to one year so you can reactivate and pick up exactly where you left off; if you do not reactivate within that period, your content is permanently deleted. You can ask us to delete your data immediately at any time, instead of waiting out the one-year window (see Section 9) — just cancel and email us. We retain limited records (such as billing and transaction records) for as long as required to meet legal, tax, and accounting obligations. If you would rather keep your domain, you can transfer it to another registrar before your term ends.</p>

      <h2>9. Your privacy rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on where you live, you may have some or all of the following rights:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — correct inaccurate or incomplete data (much of this you can do in the app).</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — delete your account and associated data ("right to be forgotten").</li>
        <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive your data in a portable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction / Objection</strong> — limit or object to certain processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — for anything based on consent (e.g., analytics/advertising cookies), at any time, without affecting prior processing.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these, email <a href="mailto:help@legacyodyssey.com">help@legacyodyssey.com</a>. We will respond within the timeframe required by applicable law (generally within 30 days). You will not be discriminated against for exercising your rights.</p>
      <p><strong>EU/UK users:</strong> you also have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority. <strong>California users (CCPA/CPRA):</strong> we do not sell your personal information, and you may request access to or deletion of your data using the contact above.</p>

      <h2>10. Your book visitors</h2>
      <p>When someone visits a published book using the password you shared, we collect minimal technical information (such as IP address and browser type) for security and performance. We do not use this to track those visitors across other websites.</p>

      <h2>11. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>The Service is intended for use by parents and legal guardians, who must be adults. Accounts may only be created and managed by an adult, and we do not knowingly allow children to create accounts or knowingly collect personal information directly from a child. A book may contain information and photos about a child, which the account holder provides and is responsible for, having the authority to do so.</p>
      <p>We design with children's privacy in mind, consistent with the U.S. Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and, where applicable, GDPR protections for children's data. If you believe a child has provided us personal information without proper authorization, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

      <h2>12. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version here with a new "Last updated" date and, for material changes, notify account holders by email.</p>

      <h2>13. Contact us</h2>
      <p>Questions or concerns about this policy or how we handle your data:</p>
